<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h4>
<p>
    This manual is a brief guide on helping administrator users in doing tasks that help properly manage and use database. This can be used only by administrators not other users.
</p>
<p>
    The <strong> administrator </strong> group can do any of the following:
    <ul>
        <li>Add New User</li>
        <li>Block/de-activate existing user(s)</li>
        <li>View existing reports</li>
        <li>Aprove/Reject reports</li>
        <li>Add/Edit Master Data such as districts, health facilities, etc.</li>
        <li>Create Pivot Table</li>
    </ul>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>But</strong> the <strong>administrators</strong> can not do:
    <ul>
        <li>Add and/or Edit reports</li>
        <li>Delete Reports</li>
    </ul>
</p>
