<h2 id="verification">Verification of reports</h2>
<p>
    It is important to check the data that is being entered into database is accurate and reliable. Having no data is better than inaccurate data. Erroneous data may lead to wrong decisions.
</p>
<p>
Data accuracy or quality of data is not responsibility of one or two persons. It is everyoneâ€™s job. The typist, tally person, head of the project. But the accuracy of NUTRITION data is mostly dependent of tally person or the base where data is gathered namely the health facility is the base of accurate and inaccurate data. 
</p>
<p>
The other person who is responsible for data quality is the person who enters data into database. He/she shall not only care about data entry while typing into database but he should make sure the data that enters into database is fine and make correction if there is any problem with the source data in the hard copy or tally. He should also make this ethic for him to double check data after every data entry of a report and regularly check quality of data using data entry forms, pivot table and provide feedback in order to minimize errors or mistakes in the data.
</p>
<p>
In this paper we focus on the accuracy check of the data entered in the database. Database is not that wise to check if 4 odema for <6 children was recorded as 4 6-24 months. But it will check that duplicate record is not entered, alarm when total number of male and female is not matching with total number of new admission in MAM and do some other validation check.
</p>
<p>
The database automatically checks that the data is entered correctly in the database and prevent errors that are already defined but it will not be sufficient then  
You may do the following precautions during review of data to monitor the quality of data entered into database:
</p>
<ul>
    <li class="small">Make sure a report is not empty or blank</li>
    <li class="small">Make sure the time and period of entered report is correct</li>
    <li class="small">Look at big number of refer in, deaths, defaulters and other</li>
    <li class="small">Make sure the total number of exits is not bigger than total admissions</li>
    <li class="small">Make sure total at the end of the month is not negative</li>
    <li class="small">If the report is complete and accurate then approve the record</li>
    <li class="small">But if the report is not complete and have error. Then reject it and provide reasons for rejection</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h2 id="nmrstatus">Approving a Report</h2>
<p>
    Every report entered by users in the provinces will be listed in this list. As you can see in the list, the status column has some colored status. 
    <p><strong style="background-color:#00C0EF;color:#FFFFFF">Processing </strong> means that the record is just entered by the user and is waiting for your review and approval</p>
    <p>
        <strong style="background-color:blue;color:#FFFFFF">Updaded</strong> means that the record was updated or modified by the user
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong style="background-color:green;color:#FFFFFF">Verified</strong> means that the record was accepted and verified by you. In this case the user will not be to make any further modification to the report.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong style="background-color:red;color:#FFFFFF">Rejected</strong> means that the report had some problem and you have rejected. In this case the user will be notified of the rejection and he/she then can look and modify if needed.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong style="background-color:red;color:#FFFFFF">Uknown</strong> If there any unknown it means that the record is migrated from old database.
    </p>
