<h2 id ="more">Care for Quality of Data</h2>
<p>
    When analyzing data you may consider the following items:
</p>
<ul>
    <li  class="small">Look for large gaps in the data</li>
    <li  class="small">Look for unusual month to month variations</li>
    <li  class="small">Question for duplication in reporting or repetitive values</li>
    <li  class="small">Check for inconsistencies â€“ unlikely values</li>
    <li  class="small">Look for data present where there should not be</li>
    <li  class="small">There might be typing errors if there is a very large data</li>
    <li  class="small">Check that data is not entered in wrong places</li>
    <li  class="small">Look for any other patterns that affects the quality of data</li>
</ul>

